The students from the Wilhelm-Heinrich-von-Riehl-School were transported to nearby hospitals. The cause of the respiratory irritation is currently unknown. Emergency services, including rescue workers, are also on the scene.  Forces from numerous fire stations, including several volunteer fire brigades, are on the scene. An eyewitness, @MihaEL_27, described seeing a "large scale operation" including fire brigade and police near the school. Writing on Twitter, they said: "@Polizei_WH what's going on in Wiesbaden right now?  "Countless ambulances + police with sirens on duty for about 1 hour. "Large-scale operation by fire brigade and police in #Biebrich #Wilhelm Heinrich von Riehl school cleared. "40 people complain of respiratory problems." 